HEADWORD: Cortile
<hw>Cor"tile</hw> <pr>(k?r"t?l; It. k?r-t?"l?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[It., fr. <ets>corte</ets> court.]</ety> <def>An open internal
courtyard inclosed by the walls of a large dwelling house or other large
and stately building.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

